# Vercel Web Analytics Implementation

## Summary
Successfully installed and configured Vercel Web Analytics for the christ-info project following the official Vercel documentation.

## Changes Made

### 1. Package Installation
- Installed `@vercel/analytics` package (version 2.0.1) using npm
- Updated `package.json` to include the new dependency
- Updated `package-lock.json` to lock dependency versions

### 2. Analytics Integration
- Modified `src/App.tsx` to import the Analytics component from `@vercel/analytics/react`
- Added `<Analytics />` component at the root level of the App component, placed after the Footer component
- This follows the official Vercel documentation for Vite/React projects

### 3. Build Verification
- Successfully built the project with no errors or warnings
- The build output confirms all modules transformed correctly
- Bundle size: 424.56 kB (gzipped: 124.20 kB)

## Implementation Details

The Analytics component was added according to Vercel's official quickstart guide for React/Vite projects. The component is placed at the root level of the application, ensuring it tracks page views across all routes handled by React Router.

## Files Modified
- `package.json` - Added @vercel/analytics dependency
- `package-lock.json` - Updated with new dependency lockfile entries
- `src/App.tsx` - Imported and added Analytics component

## Next Steps for Deployment
1. Deploy the application to Vercel using `vercel deploy`
2. Enable Web Analytics in the Vercel dashboard (Analytics sidebar → Select project → Enable)
3. Verify setup by checking the browser's Network tab for fetch requests to `/<unique-path>/view`

## Notes
- The existing code structure was preserved completely
- Only minimal, necessary changes were made
- The Analytics component is self-contained and requires no additional configuration
- Pre-existing linter configuration issues were noted but are unrelated to these changes
